  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    Both Allianz Care and BUPA Global are excellent international health insurers backed by major European insurance groups. This is a choice between two quality options, not good versus bad.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Allianz Care</strong> offers the better value for most healthy expats. You get comprehensive coverage from a financially rock-solid insurer at 30-40% lower premiums than BUPA. Their flexibility with high-deductible options makes them even more cost-effective for those willing to self-insure routine expenses. For healthy people without specific needs BUPA serves better, Allianz is the smart choice.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>BUPA Global</strong> justifies its premium pricing for specific situations. If mental health coverage is a priority—BUPA's parity approach is unmatched. If you have pre-existing conditions—BUPA's full underwriting offers possibilities Allianz's moratorium cannot. If you want all-inclusive benefits, premium service, and are willing to pay for it—BUPA delivers.
  </p>
  <p>
    Our recommendation: <strong>Start with Allianz Care</strong> as the default choice. Only upgrade to <strong>BUPA Global</strong> if you specifically need their mental health coverage, have pre-existing conditions requiring coverage, or genuinely value premium service over cost savings.
  </p>

