  <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is BUPA Global worth 30-40% more than Allianz Care?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        For most healthy expats, no. Allianz provides comprehensive coverage at significantly lower cost. BUPA is worth the premium if you specifically need their mental health parity, want pre-existing conditions underwritten, or prioritize all-inclusive benefits and premium service over cost savings.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Which provider has better mental health coverage?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        BUPA Global has dramatically better mental health coverage—it's one of their key differentiators. Full mental health parity means no separate limits for mental health treatment. Allianz covers mental health but with session caps and separate limits that may be insufficient for ongoing needs.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How do pre-existing conditions work with each provider?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        Allianz uses moratorium underwriting—pre-existing conditions are automatically excluded for 2+ years. BUPA uses full medical underwriting—they review your health history and may cover well-managed conditions from day one. <a href="/best/expat-health-insurance" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 underline">Get quotes from both</a> to see what terms each offers for your conditions.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Does BUPA's no-claims discount make up for higher premiums?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        Partially, over time. Claim-free members can earn discounts up to 50%, which narrows the price gap. But it takes years of no claims to maximize, and any claim resets the discount. For most people, the no-claims discount doesn't fully close the 30-40% gap.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Which provider is better for families?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        For healthy families, Allianz's 30-40% savings—potentially $3,600-6,000 annually for a family—is compelling. That's meaningful money for education or other priorities. BUPA makes sense for families with specific needs: a child requiring mental health support, a parent with pre-existing conditions, or planned pregnancy where higher maternity limits matter.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I switch between these providers later?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        Yes, at annual renewal. However, conditions developed on your previous policy become pre-existing for the new insurer. Switching from BUPA to Allianz means those conditions go into moratorium exclusion. Switching from Allianz to BUPA means new underwriting review. Switch carefully, especially if health has changed.
      </p>
    </div>
